race.comment: MOLONGLE SURPRISE (2) loves this track and trip with seven wins and six placings from 16 attempts. Goes well for trainer/jockey Kliese and will give backers a sight. FAMILY STAR (6) is a ten-time winner around this circuit and has been thereabouts in recent efforts. Looms as the main danger. HAND GRENADE (12) returned in good order with a solid win at Ingham and will strip fitter for that hit-out. Can go back-to-back. FROM THIS MOMENT (9) is one from one over this course and distance and has won two from four when first-up. Sure to run a race while fresh. RECRUITER (8) is a last-start winner who can feature in the finish again.
